<subSubSection id="7EE36552FFCFFFCBEB6D44BD2F214A61" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="227" pageId="3" pageNumber="226" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="364636D9FFCFFFCCEB6D44BD2B184AC1" blockId="3.[794,1399,1193,1249]" pageId="3" pageNumber="226">
<emphasis id="048DEACBFFCFFFCCEB6D44BD2DFA4AE1" bold="true" box="[794,916,1193,1217]" pageId="3" pageNumber="226">Discussion</emphasis>
: This new taxon is closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="F1F94D5AFFCFFFCCED5644BD2A734AC1" authority="(ALFKEN, 1936)" baseAuthorityName="ALFKEN" baseAuthorityYear="1936" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Hylaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="226" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trifidus">
<emphasis id="048DEACBFFCFFFCCED5644BD2D064AC1" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="226">Hylaeus trifidus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="52684B28FFCFFFCCEB0F44DD2A7B4AC1" author="ALFKEN, J. D." box="[888,1045,1225,1249]" pageId="3" pageNumber="226" pagination="1 - 24" refId="ref10306" refString="ALFKEN, J. D. 1936: Schwedisch-chinesische wissenschaftliche Expedition nach den nordwestlichen Provinzen Chinas, unter Leitung von Dr. Sven Hedin und Prof. Su Ping-chang. Insekten gesammelt vom schwedischen Arzt der Expedition Dr. David Hummel 1927 - 1930. 55. Hymnoptera, 9. Apidae. - Arkiv for Zoologi 27 A (37): 1 - 24." type="journal article" year="1936">ALFKEN, 1936</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, but it is clearly separated by its
</paragraph>
<caption id="62866651FFCFFFCCE934481F2D9D4602" box="[323,1011,2059,2082]" pageId="3" pageNumber="226" startId="3.[323,356,2059,2081]" targetBox="[322,1226,1293,2051]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph id="364636D9FFCFFFCCE934481F2D9D4602" blockId="3.[323,1011,2059,2082]" box="[323,1011,2059,2082]" pageId="3" pageNumber="226">
<emphasis id="048DEACBFFCFFFCCE934481F2F164601" bold="true" box="[323,376,2059,2081]" pageId="3" pageNumber="226">Fig. 5</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName id="F1F94D5AFFCFFFCCE9F348182C8E4601" authority="(ALFKEN)" baseAuthorityName="ALFKEN" box="[388,736,2060,2081]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Hylaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="226" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trifidus" subGenus="Hylaeus">
<emphasis id="048DEACBFFCFFFCCE9F348182FA14601" box="[388,463,2060,2081]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="226">Hylaeus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="048DEACBFFCFFFCCE9AA48182C464601" box="[477,552,2060,2081]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="226">Hylaeus</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="048DEACBFFCFFFCCEA4148182C144601" box="[566,634,2060,2081]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="226">trifidus</emphasis>
(ALFKEN)
</taxonomicName>
. Map of known distribution.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="364636D9FFC8FFCBE8CA40FE2C914F01" blockId="4.[188,796,233,1089]" pageId="4" pageNumber="227">
occurrence outside the distribution area of 
<taxonomicName id="F1F94D5AFFC8FFCBEADC40FE2D744F21" box="[683,794,233,257]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Hylaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="227" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trifidus">
<emphasis id="048DEACBFFC8FFCBEADC40FE2D744F21" box="[683,794,233,257]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="227">H. trifidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="AEC22A5CFFC8FFCBE8B2411D2F6A4F01" box="[197,260,265,289]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[323,356,2059,2081]" captionTargetBox="[322,1226,1293,2051]" captionTargetId="figure-552@3.[322,1226,1293,2051]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 5: Hylaeus (Hylaeus) trifidus (ALFKEN). Map of known distribution." pageId="4" pageNumber="227">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
) and by significant morphological differences.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="364636D9FFC8FFCBE8CA413E2FC04D41" blockId="4.[188,796,233,1089]" pageId="4" pageNumber="227">
<taxonomicName id="F1F94D5AFFC8FFCBE8CA413E2F474F61" box="[189,297,297,321]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Hylaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="227" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trifidus">
<emphasis id="048DEACBFFC8FFCBE8CA413E2F474F61" box="[189,297,297,321]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="227">H. trifidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs between the Greek Aegean Islands (Lesvos, Chios) and the 
<collectingRegion id="F43DF83BFFC8FFCBE9A7415D2C494F41" box="[464,551,329,353]" country="Turkey" name="Hakkari" pageId="4" pageNumber="227">Hakkari</collectingRegion>
Mountains mainly in the southern half of 
<collectingCountry id="4EEE7649FFC8FFCBE9DC417D2F994FA1" box="[427,503,361,385]" name="Turkey" pageId="4" pageNumber="227">Turkey</collectingCountry>
. The mark by 
<bibRefCitation id="52684B28FFC8FFCBEAD3417D2FEF4F81" author="ASCHER, J. S. &amp; PICKERING, J." pageId="4" pageNumber="227" refId="ref10373" refString="ASCHER, J. S. &amp; PICKERING, J. 2014: Hylaeus trifidus (ALFKEN, 1936). - In: Discover Life's bee species guide and world checklist (Hymenoptera: Apoidea: Anthophila). &lt;http: // www. discoverlife. org / mp / 20 m? r = 0.0125 &amp; la = 39.75 &amp; lo = 20.5 &amp; kind = Hylaeus + trifi dus&gt; Accessed 5 June 2015." type="url" year="2014">ASCHER &amp; PICKERING (2014)</bibRefCitation>
on the Greek mainland is a centroid point for 
<collectingCountry id="4EEE7649FFC8FFCBE95441BD2F014FE1" box="[291,367,425,449]" name="Greece" pageId="4" pageNumber="227">Greece</collectingCountry>
, not to be interpreted as local specimen record (ASCHER, personal communication). The species is not distributed north of latitude 
<geoCoordinate id="53CD501EFFC8FFCBEA5F41FD2C0F4C21" box="[552,609,489,513]" degrees="40" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="4" pageNumber="227" precision="55555" value="40.0">40°N</geoCoordinate>
. To the South, the species occurs along the eastern Mediterranean coastal region of 
<collectingCountry id="4EEE7649FFC8FFCBE950423D2FE84C61" box="[295,390,553,577]" name="Palestine" pageId="4" pageNumber="227">Palestine</collectingCountry>
and reaches the northern part of the Negev desert in 
<collectingCountry id="4EEE7649FFC8FFCBE906425D2FC54C41" box="[369,427,585,609]" name="Israel" pageId="4" pageNumber="227">Israel</collectingCountry>
at approximately 
<geoCoordinate id="53CD501EFFC8FFCBEA19425D2CC84C41" box="[622,678,585,609]" degrees="31" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="4" pageNumber="227" precision="55555" value="31.0">31°N</geoCoordinate>
, but is not found further south in 
<collectingCountry id="4EEE7649FFC8FFCBE9C1427E2F994CA2" box="[438,503,618,642]" name="Egypt" pageId="4" pageNumber="227">Egypt</collectingCountry>
. A record from 
<collectingCountry id="4EEE7649FFC8FFCBEAD7427E2CA34CA1" box="[672,717,618,641]" name="Iran" pageId="4" pageNumber="227">Iran</collectingCountry>
(“ 
<collectingRegion id="F43DF83BFFC8FFCBEA93427D2E8D4C81" country="Iran" name="Esfahan" pageId="4" pageNumber="227">Ispahan</collectingRegion>
”, 
<bibRefCitation id="52684B28FFC8FFCBE88E429D2FA74C81" author="WARNCKE, K." box="[249,457,649,673]" pageId="4" pageNumber="227" pagination="746 - 768" refId="ref12213" refString="WARNCKE, K. 1972: Beitrag zur Systematik und Verbreitung der Bienengattung Prosopis F. in der Westpalaarktis (Hymenoptera, Apoidea, Colletidae). - Bulletin des Recherches agronomique de Gembloux, N. S. 5: 746 - 768." type="book chapter" year="1972">Warncke 1972: 753</bibRefCitation>
) has been corrected (
<bibRefCitation id="52684B28FFC8FFCBEACE429D2F464CE1" author="WARNCKE, K." pageId="4" pageNumber="227" pagination="145 - 195" refId="ref12258" refString="WARNCKE, K. 1981: Beitrag zur Bienenfauna des Iran 12. Die Gattung Prosopis F., mit Bemerkungen zu weiteren bekannten und unbekannten palaarktischen Arten. - Bollettino del Museo Civico di Storia naturale di Venezia 31 (1980): 145 - 195." type="journal article" year="1981">Warncke 1981: 191</bibRefCitation>
, “ 
<collectingRegion id="F43DF83BFFC8FFCBE93742BD2FFD4CE1" box="[320,403,681,705]" country="Iran" name="Esfahan" pageId="4" pageNumber="227">Isfahan</collectingRegion>
”). However, it can be assumed that there was once a larger common area of distribution of 
<taxonomicName id="F1F94D5AFFC8FFCBE8AA42FE2F234D21" box="[221,333,745,769]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Hylaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="227" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trifidus">
<emphasis id="048DEACBFFC8FFCBE8AA42FE2F234D21" box="[221,333,745,769]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="227">H. trifidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
populations, of which the southern ones became isolated (perhaps by desert conditions), and that it survived only on the mountainous “island” of Mt Katharine in the Sinai.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="364636D9FFC8FFCBE8CA437D2F214A61" blockId="4.[188,796,233,1089]" pageId="4" pageNumber="227">
Morphologically, the head of 
<taxonomicName id="F1F94D5AFFC8FFCBE989437E2C0C4DA1" authorityName="Dathe" authorityYear="2015" box="[510,610,873,897]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Hylaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="227" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oliviae">
<emphasis id="048DEACBFFC8FFCBE989437E2C0C4DA1" box="[510,610,873,897]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="227">H. oliviae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
females is much longer and narrower than that of 
<taxonomicName id="F1F94D5AFFC8FFCBEA5A439E2CF74D81" box="[557,665,905,929]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Hylaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="227" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trifidus">
<emphasis id="048DEACBFFC8FFCBEA5A439E2CF74D81" box="[557,665,905,929]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="227">H. trifidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; this points to a special adaptation to a different flower shape, i.e. an independent, divergent evolution. Norfolk et al. (in preparation) report flower visiting on 
<taxonomicName id="F1F94D5AFFC8FFCBEA3A43FD2E9E4A01" authority="Mill." authorityName="Mill." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Foeniculum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="227" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vulgare">
<emphasis id="048DEACBFFC8FFCBEA3A43FD2D774A21" box="[589,793,1001,1025]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="227">Foeniculum vulgare</emphasis>
Mill.
</taxonomicName>
(60 %) and 
<taxonomicName id="F1F94D5AFFC8FFCBE91A441D2CDD4A01" authority="FRESEN" authorityName="FRESEN" box="[365,691,1033,1057]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Anarrhinum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="227" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pubescens">
<emphasis id="048DEACBFFC8FFCBE91A441D2C304A01" box="[365,606,1033,1057]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="227">Anarrhinum pubescens</emphasis>
FRESEN
</taxonomicName>
(40 %) in June and July.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
